{% endif %}

===== PLAYER ACTION =====
"{{ player_action }}"

===== INSTRUCTIONS =====
Determine:
1. Is this a combat action? (attacking, fighting, striking, shooting, etc.)
2. Which NPC(s) is the player targeting?
3. Does the player have advantage (surprise, flanking, high ground)?
4. Does the player have disadvantage (blinded, restrained, prone)?
5. Would any other NPCs present join the fight against the player?
   (hostile NPCs, allies of the target, guards reacting to violence)

Respond ONLY in JSON:
{
  "is_combat": true/false,
  "targets": [{"npc_id": "...", "npc_name": "..."}],
  "player_has_advantage": true/false,
  "player_has_disadvantage": true/false,
  "npcs_join_fight": [{"npc_id": "...", "npc_name": "..."}],
  "context": "brief explanation of the combat situation"
}

If this is NOT a combat action (talking, trading, investigating, etc.),
return is_combat=false with empty targets.
